<subSubSection id="3DE201D1816A7D4CA749CBDC5876EB7F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="10855FF6BAE40BC4A6E80F4FD718B223" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D77356F717FDFED6F646E0AE42C729DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="FF1A98FDA6453BDBBF48FC6C8893EE5A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="91476B624D013C73B1D3D7409A58387C" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Distribution maps of Neotropical Nilothauma species A N. fittkaui (Soponis, 1987), N. amazonense Mendes &amp; Andersen, 2009 B N. aripuanense Mendes &amp; Andersen, 2009, N Nilothauma aleta Roback, 1960 C N. reissi (Soponis, 1987), N. soka Andersen, Bello-Gonzalez &amp; Hagenlund, 2016 D N. anamariae Dantas &amp; Hamada, 2017, N. jaraguaense Mendes &amp; Andersen, 2009." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1033.60686.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534710" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">17A</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
The species was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="1E0AC84A782C8EC467E8EAB3FC6C6D74" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/01650528709360715" author="Soponis, AR" journalOrPublisher="Studies on Neotropical Fauna and Environment" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="11 - 24" refId="B16" refString="Soponis, AR, 1987. Paranilothauma and Neelamia, new genera of Chironomini (Diptera: Chironomidae) from Brazil. Studies on Neotropical Fauna and Environment 22: 11 - 24, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/01650528709360715" title="Paranilothauma and Neelamia, new genera of Chironomini (Diptera: Chironomidae) from Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/01650528709360715" volume="22" year="1987">Soponis (1987)</bibRefCitation>
from Amazonas and later recorded from Acre, 
<normalizedToken id="F13321356033F20EEA8849364C3A24AD" originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo and Para States in Brazil and from Ecuador by 
<bibRefCitation id="69E19E7ABFC1EB59B3A7915222A13503" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2063.1.1" author="Mendes, HF" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 45" refId="B8" refString="Mendes, HF, Andersen, T, 2009. Neotropical Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921, with the description of thirteen new species (Diptera: Chironomidae). Zootaxa 2063: 1 - 45, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2063.1.1" title="Neotropical Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921, with the description of thirteen new species (Diptera: Chironomidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2063.1.1" volume="2063" year="2009">Mendes and Andersen (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. The range is now extended south to 
<normalizedToken id="96B6482512BFFE5287CC1A8A973A2411" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo State in Brazil and north to Costa Rica in Central America.
</paragraph>
